en_229395_0	The search and rescue mission for the 17-year-old boy who went missing following the earth slip  that destroyed  a house in Malapattawa area in Walapane, Nuwara Eliya, enters the second day.
en_229395_1	The police stated that the Walapane Police and the Army have commenced a search operation from 6 am this morning with the improvement of the prevailing weather conditions.
en_229395_2	The search operation was temporarily halted yesterday as a result of the earth slips caused by heavy rains.
en_229395_3	The mother, father and daughter of the same family were killed when the land slide destroyed the house completely while they were in the house on Saturday night.
en_229395_4	Their bodies were recovered yesterday morning.
